<subSubSection id="C331653CB939E50A3A948FD7FC16FDC1" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9436B7B939E50A3A948FD7FD75FE6E" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,524]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A3A948FD7FEE9FF7C" bold="true" box="[199,317,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Remarks:</emphasis>
The short, sharp armature of the anterior pronotal lobe results in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B939E50A3E658FD7FB19FF7D" authority="Swanson, 2021" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" box="[1078,1229,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A3E658FD7FB19FF7D" box="[1078,1229,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Heza graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A3E858FD7FAE6FF7C" bold="true" box="[1238,1330,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C57DEB939E50A3E858FD7FAE6FF7C" box="[1238,1330,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
reaching couplet # 
<quantity id="4CD39B52B939E50A3B538FF9FEEDFF1E" box="[256,313,185,211]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" unit="in" value="23.0">23 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B939E50A3B138FF9FDF1FF19" author="Maldonado" box="[320,549,185,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado’s (1976)</bibRefCitation>
key. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B939E50A39E28FFAFA93FF1E" authority="Maldonado, 1976" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[945,1351,185,211]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubromarga">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A39E28FFAFBADFF1E" box="[945,1145,185,211]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Heza rubromarga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B939E50A3ED28FF9FA93FF1E" author="Maldonado" box="[1153,1351,185,211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">
Maldonado, 
<quantity id="4CD39B52B939E50A3F5C8FF9FA93FF1E" box="[1295,1351,185,211]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0190399999999995" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" unit="in" value="1976.0">1976</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in possessing a taller median process of the pygophore with sinuate lateral margins. The recurved apical fold also is narrower than the base in the new species. Despite being characterized as having only the first connexivum spined by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B939E50A3AC48E61FEB8FEF1" author="Maldonado" box="[151,364,289,316]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B939E50A3B298E61FDDBFEF6" author="Kirby, W. F." box="[378,527,289,315]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="71 - 73" refId="ref8432" refString="Kirby, W. F. (1900) Hymenoptera, Hemiptera Heteroptera, Homoptera, Neuroptera, and Orthoptera. In: Report on a collection made by Messrs. F. V. McConnell and J. J. Quelch at Mount Roraima in British Guiana. The Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 8 (2), pp. 71 - 73." type="journal article" year="1900">Kirby (1900)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B939E50A38DF8E62FC3CFEF6" authority="(Kirby, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[652,1000,289,315]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perarmata">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A38DF8E62FC91FEF6" box="[652,837,290,315]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Heza perarmata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B939E50A39068E61FC0BFEF6" author="Kirby, W. F." box="[853,991,289,315]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="71 - 73" refId="ref8432" refString="Kirby, W. F. (1900) Hymenoptera, Hemiptera Heteroptera, Homoptera, Neuroptera, and Orthoptera. In: Report on a collection made by Messrs. F. V. McConnell and J. J. Quelch at Mount Roraima in British Guiana. The Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 8 (2), pp. 71 - 73." type="journal article" year="1900">Kirby, 1900</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
as having “Abdominal segments with four small lateral spines on the basal half”; thus, I have concluded that Maldonado misidentified 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B939E50A3E9F8E05FAB7FE93" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1228,1379,325,350]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perarmata">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A3E9F8E05FAB7FE93" box="[1228,1379,325,350]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">H. perarmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B939E50A3B2C8E27FDCCFE4D" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[383,536,359,384]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perarmata">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A3B2C8E27FDCCFE4D" box="[383,536,359,384]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">H. perarmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B939E50A38688E27FCCDFE4C" author="Maldonado" box="[571,793,359,385]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado’s (1976</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 51–52) treatment still differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B939E50A3EB38E27FA82FE4D" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" box="[1248,1366,359,384]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A3EB38E27FA82FE4D" box="[1248,1366,359,384]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">H. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the median process of the pygophore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9436B7B939E50A3A948EECFC16FDC1" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,524]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">
The general habitus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B939E50A3B988EEDFCB9FE0A" authority="(Lichtenstein, 1796)" baseAuthorityName="Lichtenstein" baseAuthorityYear="1796" box="[459,877,428,455]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippium">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A3B988EEDFD56FE0B" box="[459,642,428,454]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Heza ephippium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B939E50A38C28EECFCB1FE0A" author="Lichtenstein, A. A. H." box="[657,869,428,455]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" refId="ref8590" refString="Lichtenstein, A. A. H. (1796) Catalogus musei zoologici ditissimi Hamburgi, d. III. Februar 1796 auctionis lege distrahendi. Sectio Tertia. Continens Insecta. Schniebes, Hamburg, 224 pp." type="book" year="1796">Lichtenstein, 1796</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B939E50A39F68EEDFB7CFE0A" authority="Stal, 1859" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1859" box="[933,1192,428,455]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A39F68EEDFBFBFE0B" box="[933,1071,428,454]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Heza similis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B939E50A3E658EECFB7CFE0A" author="Stal, C." box="[1078,1192,428,455]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="175 - 204" refId="ref8807" refString="Stal, C. (1859) Till kannedomen om Reduvini. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 16 (10), 175 - 204." type="journal article" year="1859">Stål, 1859</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
looks similar, but the armature of the anterior pronotal lobe of those species is medium-sized and apically blunted and the short, robust, truncate median process of the pygophore differs markedly in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B939E50A39038EB2FC6FFDC6" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1859" box="[848,955,497,523]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B939E50A39038EB2FC6FFDC6" box="[848,955,497,523]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">H. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
